00:19:52.985 --> 00:19:54.145
that the 100-Year Building

00:19:54.225 --> 00:19:57.745
has been renovated properly, according
to all civil engineering standards.

00:19:58.265 --> 00:19:59.585
You can rest easy.

00:20:00.105 --> 00:20:02.105
All the rumors circulating in this school

00:20:02.625 --> 00:20:03.945
are fake news.

00:20:07.305 --> 00:20:10.265
So, if you don't believe an engineer,

00:20:10.345 --> 00:20:12.145
who will you believe?

00:20:12.665 --> 00:20:13.825
Exactly.

00:20:13.905 --> 00:20:19.025
Therefore, what these two did
deserves expulsion.

00:20:19.105 --> 00:20:20.385
Shit.

00:20:22.185 --> 00:20:23.025
Expel them.

00:20:23.105 --> 00:20:24.545
-Yeah, expel them.
-Expel?

00:20:25.585 --> 00:20:26.585
But…

00:20:27.105 --> 00:20:28.985
I'm a kind person.

00:20:29.065 --> 00:20:31.425
I can't just expel them like that.

00:20:31.505 --> 00:20:34.345
So I'd like to give them one more chance.

00:20:34.985 --> 00:20:37.185
Potae, open it.

00:20:41.945 --> 00:20:44.665
This is the face of the Exclamation group

00:20:45.825 --> 00:20:49.185
that spreads fake news
to destroy our school.

00:20:49.265 --> 00:20:51.425
Now you've all seen

00:20:51.505 --> 00:20:54.145
how many of them there are, right?

00:20:55.425 --> 00:20:56.465
One.

00:20:57.185 --> 00:20:58.345
Two.

00:20:59.465 --> 00:21:00.345
Three.

00:21:00.865 --> 00:21:01.705
Four.

00:21:01.785 --> 00:21:03.465
And five.

00:21:04.625 --> 00:21:06.225
The other three members

00:21:06.745 --> 00:21:08.905
are standing here right now, right?

00:21:09.425 --> 00:21:12.905
If either of you can tell me

00:21:13.425 --> 00:21:14.945
who the other three are,

00:21:16.145 --> 00:21:17.825
I will regard you as witnesses.

00:21:18.345 --> 00:21:20.585
That means
you won't receive any punishment.

00:21:21.665 --> 00:21:25.305
No, remember our ideals. Don't do it.

00:21:28.865 --> 00:21:31.425
You don't need to say their names.

00:21:31.945 --> 00:21:33.745
Just point at them.

00:21:42.385 --> 00:21:44.105
No, don't do it.

00:21:44.185 --> 00:21:45.145
Just point.

00:21:45.225 --> 00:21:46.865
-Remember our ideals.
-Come on.

00:21:51.065 --> 00:21:52.665
Point.

00:21:53.425 --> 00:21:54.305
Tell us.

00:21:57.065 --> 00:21:57.905
Hey, No.

00:22:01.105 --> 00:22:02.305
Point.

00:22:09.465 --> 00:22:10.665
Hey, No!

00:22:11.185 --> 00:22:12.225
Don't do it.

00:22:14.945 --> 00:22:16.105
Point at them.

00:22:16.185 --> 00:22:17.145
Point at them.

00:22:19.865 --> 00:22:21.065
Hey?

00:22:21.145 --> 00:22:22.225
-Potae?
-Potae?

00:22:22.305 --> 00:22:24.625
-Really?
-Really?

00:22:24.705 --> 00:22:26.385
-Damn you.
-You? What the hell?

00:22:29.225 --> 00:22:31.225
Down with the corrupt!

00:22:31.305 --> 00:22:33.145
Long live Exclamation!

00:22:33.745 --> 00:22:35.105
Do it for me.

00:22:35.185 --> 00:22:36.745
Destroy them.

00:22:36.825 --> 00:22:38.145
Ugh!

00:22:38.665 --> 00:22:41.785
These two are hereby expelled
from Bangkwai School immediately.

00:22:41.865 --> 00:22:42.865
Take them away.

00:22:42.945 --> 00:22:44.945
Get out. Get out.

00:22:45.025 --> 00:22:46.745
-Get out.
-Damn, No. I love you.

00:22:47.505 --> 00:22:49.825
Get out. Get out.

00:22:53.785 --> 00:22:54.665
Get out.

00:22:54.745 --> 00:22:56.665
IN 20 DAYS

00:22:56.745 --> 00:22:58.665
IN 19 DAYS

00:23:02.425 --> 00:23:06.585
NO ENTRY

00:23:20.265 --> 00:23:21.585
5:30 P.M. - THIRD FLOOR COMPUTER ROOM

00:23:21.665 --> 00:23:22.545
What do we do now?

00:23:24.105 --> 00:23:25.825
We have to do it for Nobel and Tae.

00:23:25.905 --> 00:23:29.505
We have to stop
the 100-Year Building from opening.

00:23:30.225 --> 00:23:32.465
But our futures matter too.

00:23:32.545 --> 00:23:34.225
If I get expelled now,

00:23:34.745 --> 00:23:36.025
my dad will kill me.

00:23:36.105 --> 00:23:39.705
But if the 100-Year Building collapses,
we'll be dead too.

00:23:40.345 --> 00:23:41.345
And in that case…

00:23:41.985 --> 00:23:43.065
we'd be dead for real.

00:23:46.225 --> 00:23:49.065
The engineer already confirmed

00:23:49.145 --> 00:23:51.385
that the building won't collapse.

00:23:51.465 --> 00:23:53.465
You actually believe that headmaster?

00:23:54.865 --> 00:23:57.305
You saw the condition yourself.
Did you forget already?

00:23:57.385 --> 00:23:59.185
But we're not engineers.

00:23:59.985 --> 00:24:02.145
Even if it really collapsed,

00:24:02.225 --> 00:24:03.945
no one would care anyway.

00:24:05.585 --> 00:24:09.065
Why should we gamble our futures for this?

00:24:12.105 --> 00:24:13.385
It's okay, Beng.

00:24:15.185 --> 00:24:17.825
If you're not comfortable with this
or if you want to quit…

00:24:20.825 --> 00:24:21.905
I understand.

00:24:31.465 --> 00:24:38.145
BANGKWAI WITTHAYAKHOM'S 100-YEAR BUILDING

00:24:44.025 --> 00:24:46.345
Even if it really did collapse,

00:24:46.425 --> 00:24:48.425
no one would care anyway.

00:24:51.025 --> 00:24:55.265
NO ENTRY

00:25:04.425 --> 00:25:07.465
5:30 P.M. - THIRD FLOOR COMPUTER ROOM

00:25:10.905 --> 00:25:13.145
5:39 P.M.

00:25:28.905 --> 00:25:32.265
Sorry. I ran into some Scouts,
so I had to take a detour.

00:25:34.785 --> 00:25:35.985
I thought you weren't coming.

00:25:38.225 --> 00:25:39.185
Shall we start?

00:25:39.705 --> 00:25:40.745
Sure.

00:25:46.065 --> 00:25:47.105
What was that sound?

00:26:09.465 --> 00:26:11.145
Ugh, not her again.

00:26:11.225 --> 00:26:12.825
Did you bring Nanno here too?

00:26:14.265 --> 00:26:16.745
I didn't bring her. I came alone.

00:26:16.825 --> 00:26:19.745
You're telling me
you came in and didn't see her?

00:26:20.265 --> 00:26:21.305
Listen to me first, Wanda.

00:26:21.385 --> 00:26:23.265
Pankham, I can't stand you anymore.

00:26:23.345 --> 00:26:25.425
I can't believe you brought Nanno here.

00:26:27.705 --> 00:26:29.785
Nanno, how long have you been there?

00:26:30.745 --> 00:26:31.985
And how did you know we were meeting here?

00:26:32.065 --> 00:26:33.985
What's wrong with you, Pankham?

00:26:35.105 --> 00:26:36.625
You're still talking to her?

00:26:37.265 --> 00:26:39.825
She already got
two of our friends expelled.

00:26:41.505 --> 00:26:42.705
Wait, Wanda.

00:26:42.785 --> 00:26:44.825
I have something to show you.

00:26:55.225 --> 00:26:56.385
How did you get this?

00:26:58.065 --> 00:26:59.785
I was hiding in that room.

00:27:00.305 --> 00:27:02.305
Just like I was hiding in this one.

00:27:03.105 --> 00:27:06.785
You didn't even know I was here.

00:27:10.665 --> 00:27:12.025
I'll send it to you.

00:27:18.705 --> 00:27:21.305
If the Exclamation group
releases this clip,

00:27:21.905 --> 00:27:23.945
they're finished.

00:27:37.585 --> 00:27:40.105
The engineer who spoke earlier was fake.

00:27:40.185 --> 00:27:42.985
It was actually Potae
from the Scout group,

00:27:43.985 --> 00:27:45.545
deepfaking someone's face.

00:27:46.185 --> 00:27:48.345
-And the person behind it is…
-I am the engineer.

00:27:48.425 --> 00:27:49.985
I assure all students…

00:27:50.985 --> 00:27:53.225
If they keep insisting
on opening the building,

00:27:53.825 --> 00:27:54.825
it will collapse for sure.

00:27:54.905 --> 00:27:56.665
#CORRUPTRENOVATIONWILLKILLUSALL

00:27:56.745 --> 00:27:58.745
IN 17 DAYS

00:27:58.825 --> 00:28:00.665
Guys, come look at this.

00:28:00.745 --> 00:28:02.585
The engineer was fake.

00:28:04.705 --> 00:28:05.625
I told you.

00:28:08.065 --> 00:28:09.425
Shit.

00:28:17.185 --> 00:28:19.025
Deputy Kai is corrupt.

00:28:19.105 --> 00:28:20.585
They even used AI to fake an engineer?

00:28:20.665 --> 00:28:22.985
-Then the headmaster is corrupt too?
-One hundred percent.

00:28:29.585 --> 00:28:32.505
IN 16 DAYS

00:28:32.585 --> 00:28:34.465
That Exclamation group
still hasn't given up.

00:28:35.065 --> 00:28:36.985
Our students aren't even
paying attention to this anymore.

00:28:37.065 --> 00:28:38.545
But the pillar is right there.

00:28:51.305 --> 00:28:52.785
And the repair budget is already used up.

00:28:52.865 --> 00:28:54.465
I don't want the headmaster to find out.

00:28:58.105 --> 00:29:00.185
Maybe the sacred spirits can help.

00:29:02.785 --> 00:29:06.825
HAVING A JOB AND A SALARY ISN'T
AS IMPORTANT AS HAVING GOOD COWORKERS

00:29:07.745 --> 00:29:10.945
Taetae and BB broke up
because of a third person.

00:29:11.025 --> 00:29:11.985
Hey, who is it?

00:29:12.065 --> 00:29:13.825
Did someone really cause them to breakup?

00:29:18.505 --> 00:29:22.545
BB blocked Taetae. Or maybe someone
used black magic on them.

00:29:22.625 --> 00:29:23.465
Do they really have to do this?

00:29:23.545 --> 00:29:26.065
How can we help them?

00:29:30.065 --> 00:29:34.585
The Sacred 100-Year Pillar
grants every wish.

00:29:36.785 --> 00:29:40.745
Twisting the truth and diverting attention

00:29:42.345 --> 00:29:45.865
are the art of those who control the game.

00:29:51.185 --> 00:29:52.265
What are you doing?

00:29:52.345 --> 00:29:55.425
The school said this pillar is sacred.
Don't you know?

00:29:55.505 --> 00:29:56.905
Everyone in this school knows that.

00:30:02.145 --> 00:30:04.825
Nanno, whose side are you actually on?

00:30:10.265 --> 00:30:13.745
IN 5 DAYS

00:30:34.785 --> 00:30:35.785
Take it.

00:30:46.065 --> 00:30:47.665
Maybe this is all we can do.

00:30:53.745 --> 00:30:55.105
Honestly, I've been thinking.

00:30:55.625 --> 00:30:57.385
What are we even doing all this for?

00:30:57.465 --> 00:30:59.385
No one cares.

00:31:02.305 --> 00:31:05.065
But I want us to be wrong now.

00:31:07.305 --> 00:31:09.745
Maybe that building
is actually strong enough.

00:31:11.305 --> 00:31:13.345
Maybe we're just being paranoid.

00:31:18.265 --> 00:31:21.625
IN 1 DAY

00:31:30.625 --> 00:31:33.585
Today is a special day as we finally
reopen our 100-Year school building

00:31:33.665 --> 00:31:35.625
after a long renovation.

00:31:36.305 --> 00:31:38.625
The headmaster will now cut the ribbon
to officially open the building.

00:31:39.225 --> 00:31:42.065
Students, please follow the arranged lines

00:31:42.145 --> 00:31:43.705
and walk into the building in order.

00:31:43.785 --> 00:31:46.105
Your homeroom teachers will lead the way.

00:31:46.185 --> 00:31:47.745
Headmaster, please cut the ribbon.

00:31:47.825 --> 00:31:49.305
Ready?

00:32:04.305 --> 00:32:06.425
-Headmaster, this way, please.
-Alright.

00:32:06.505 --> 00:32:07.745
Mr. Dobby, let's go.

00:32:09.465 --> 00:32:11.145
All the materials used were brand new.

00:32:11.225 --> 00:32:14.105
Students, please line up
before entering the building.

00:32:14.185 --> 00:32:16.465
There are signs inside.

00:32:16.545 --> 00:32:18.185
Go directly to your classrooms.

00:32:18.265 --> 00:32:19.705
First row, you may proceed.

00:32:40.585 --> 00:32:42.665
What are we even doing all this for?

00:32:43.265 --> 00:32:44.825
No one cares.

00:32:46.145 --> 00:32:48.025
Even if it really did collapse,

00:32:48.105 --> 00:32:49.945
no one would care anyway.

00:32:53.505 --> 00:32:56.425
The famous couple has broken up.

00:32:58.225 --> 00:32:59.665
Twisting the truth

00:33:00.345 --> 00:33:02.185
and diverting attention

00:33:02.705 --> 00:33:06.065
are the art of those who control the game.

00:33:10.825 --> 00:33:12.705
Now, Pankham.

00:33:30.985 --> 00:33:32.385
BB, come with me.

00:33:32.465 --> 00:33:33.425
-What?
-Hurry.

00:33:39.225 --> 00:33:41.145
Are you excited? Hmm?

00:33:43.345 --> 00:33:44.185
Alright.

00:33:44.265 --> 00:33:46.025
I was thinking of putting
a photo here, Headmaster.

00:33:46.105 --> 00:33:48.145
Oh, what photo?

00:33:48.225 --> 00:33:50.145
Let's discuss it in your new office.

00:33:50.865 --> 00:33:52.265
-Sure.
-Please go upstairs.

00:33:52.785 --> 00:33:55.025
The photo would lead people
to your office.

00:33:55.105 --> 00:33:56.025
Oh, alright.

00:33:57.665 --> 00:33:58.865
BB, hurry.

00:33:59.385 --> 00:34:00.705
What the hell?

00:34:03.385 --> 00:34:04.945
Why did you block Taetae?

00:34:05.025 --> 00:34:06.465
And why did you delete
the photos from Instagram?

00:34:06.545 --> 00:34:07.705
It's none of your business.

00:34:11.705 --> 00:34:13.385
Your office is on the top floor.

00:34:13.465 --> 00:34:15.105
The view from up there is great.

00:34:16.545 --> 00:34:18.744
What did Taetae do to make you angry?
Tell me.

00:34:18.824 --> 00:34:21.585
Oh, did Taetae send you?

00:34:21.665 --> 00:34:22.905
Hey, answer my question.

00:34:22.985 --> 00:34:24.025
What did he do to make you mad?

00:34:24.105 --> 00:34:25.145
-Just say it.
-Are you crazy?

00:34:25.225 --> 00:34:26.705
Hey! What are you doing?

00:34:34.744 --> 00:34:35.744
BB.

00:34:36.264 --> 00:34:37.385
I'm sorry.

00:34:37.945 --> 00:34:40.425
Can we get back together?

00:34:43.425 --> 00:34:44.304
Hey.

00:34:44.385 --> 00:34:46.344
BB and Taetae.

00:34:46.425 --> 00:34:47.264
Let's go.

00:34:52.505 --> 00:34:53.784
It's so beautiful.

00:34:59.425 --> 00:35:00.625
Why do I feel dizzy?

00:35:00.705 --> 00:35:02.905
Maybe it's because the pressure
in my ears is uneven.

00:35:21.225 --> 00:35:22.665
Don't do this.

00:35:23.185 --> 00:35:24.545
The whole school is watching us.

00:35:54.105 --> 00:35:55.105
Mr. Dobby.

00:36:19.825 --> 00:36:21.345
Deputy Kai,

00:36:21.425 --> 00:36:23.905
is this building really safe?

00:36:25.945 --> 00:36:27.105
Yes, it is.

00:36:46.625 --> 00:36:48.785
Everyone, go! Hurry!

00:36:49.305 --> 00:36:51.545
Everyone, run! Hurry!

00:36:51.625 --> 00:36:52.545
Run!

00:36:52.625 --> 00:36:55.825
Everyone, run! Move.

00:37:19.145 --> 00:37:20.145
Here.

00:37:30.425 --> 00:37:31.745
The 100-Year Building…

00:37:39.145 --> 00:37:43.625
It has now become a monument
to the Exclamation group.

00:37:58.865 --> 00:38:01.105
Have you thanked me yet?

00:38:01.745 --> 00:38:04.305
I should thank you too, Pankham,

00:38:04.385 --> 00:38:06.185
for your cooperation.

00:39:06.745 --> 00:39:08.585
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, NANNO?
THE SKY IS NICE TODAY.

00:39:08.665 --> 00:39:10.385
HELLO, SKY. THE SKY IS NICE TODAY.

00:39:36.825 --> 00:39:38.225
Because the school's interests

00:39:38.305 --> 00:39:40.585
must be the same
as the students' interests.

00:39:41.185 --> 00:39:42.425
Hello.

00:39:42.505 --> 00:39:43.945
I'm Nanno. My number is two.

00:39:44.025 --> 00:39:47.865
My policy is "One Idea, One Kiss."

00:39:48.985 --> 00:39:51.145
-Nanno. Nanno.
-We found evidence of fraud

00:39:51.225 --> 00:39:53.585
in the student council election.

00:39:53.665 --> 00:39:56.745
Humans tend to repeat the same mistakes
over and over again.

00:39:56.825 --> 00:39:58.785
What makes you think
you're better than everyone else?

00:39:59.665 --> 00:40:01.705
CONGRATULATIONS, MR. PARADON TANGNAITHAM,
66TH STUDENT COUNCIL PRESIDENT

00:41:57.945 --> 00:42:01.945
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon